<h1 style="text-align:center"><%= link_to image_tag("icon", width: "15%"), "#sign_in_panel" %>Text Tagger</h1>
<br>
<h4 style="text-align:justify; color:gray"> This project uses Ruby on Rails as a resource provider to classify/tag user input with a pre-trained machine learning model (LDA). The python model is triggered by the "Tag" button under reviews/:id and will not affect the presentation of other resources. Please run the following commands to install necessary python 3 packages first:</h4>
<h4><li>pip install numpy pandas nltk scikit-learn lda</li>
<li>python -m nltk.downloader popular</li></h4>


<br>
<br>
<div class="row">
	<div class="col-sm-4">
		<div class="panel panel-default">
  			<div class="panel-heading">
    			<h3 class="panel-title"> Sample Account(s) </h3>
			</div>
			<ul class="list-group"> 
   				<li class="list-group-item"> Email: admin@example.com <br>Password: admin</li>
   			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-8">
		<div class="panel panel-info">
			<div class="panel-heading"  id="sign_in_panel">
    			<h3 class="panel-title"> Login </h3>
			</div>
			<div class="panel-body">
				<%= form_tag("/sessions", method: 'post') do  %>
				    <div class="form-group">
						<%= label_tag :email, "Email" %>
						<%= text_field_tag :email, "", autofocus: true, class: 'form-control' %>
					</div>
				    <div class="form-group">
      					<%= label_tag :password, "Password" %>
      					<%= password_field_tag :password, "", class: 'form-control' %>
					</div>
					<%= submit_tag "Sign In", class: 'btn btn-info'%> 
					or  
					<%= link_to "Sign Up", "/users/new" %>
				<% end %>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>



</div>
